{
  "bookId": "laozi-heshanggong-wiki",
  "num": 51,
  "title": "第五十一章（養德）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "道生之，"
    },
    {
      "text": "德畜之，"
    },
    {
      "text": "物形之，"
    },
    {
      "text": "勢成之。"
    },
    {
      "text": "是以萬物莫不尊道而貴德。"
    },
    {
      "text": "道之尊，德之貴，夫莫之命而常自然。"
    },
    {
      "text": "故道生之，德畜之，長之育之，成之孰之，養之覆之。"
    },
    {
      "text": "生而不有，"
    },
    {
      "text": "為而不恃，"
    },
    {
      "text": "長而不宰，"
    },
    {
      "text": "是謂玄德。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道生萬物。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "德，一也。一主布氣而蓄養。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "一為萬物設形像也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "一為萬物作寒暑之勢以成之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道德所為，無不盡驚動，而尊敬之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 17
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道一不命召萬物，而常自然應之如影響。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道之於萬物，非但生而已，乃復長養、成孰、覆育，全其性命。人君治國治身，亦當如是也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道生萬物，不有所取以為利也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道所施為，不恃望其報也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 9,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道長養萬物，不宰割以為利也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 10,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道之所行恩德，玄闇不可得見。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
